Sluicio uses a mixed licensing model.

- The product itself (the `services/`, `pkg/`, `frontend/`, and
  `deploy/` directories, among others) is licensed under the
  Functional Source License v1.1 with an Apache 2.0 future grant
  (FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0). See LICENSE-FSL.

- Peripheral code intended to be built on by third parties (the
  `plugins/` contracts, the `deploy/helm/cell/` chart, the
  `deploy/otel-collector/` config, `docs/`, and the `e2e/` suite) is
  licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. See LICENSE-APACHE.

- The `ee/` directory (Enterprise Software) is licensed separately
  under the Sluicio Enterprise License. See ee/LICENSE.md.

The authoritative per-directory mapping is in NOTICE. Source files
include SPDX-License-Identifier headers that override anything implied
by their containing directory.
